** This is a Permanent Full-time position based in Brisbane. **

** AEMO at the Heart of Energy **

We are the Australian Energy Market Operator (AEMO), committed to designing
and operating a sustainable energy system that delivers safe, reliable, and
affordable electricity and gas. Our mission includes facilitating the
transition to a net-zero energy system by 2050, working collaboratively with
industry partners to achieve 100% renewable generation capability by 2025. We
have the once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to co-design the future of our energy
systems, and our core values revolve around ** Character, Commitment, and
Connection ** .

Join us, as we contribute to this significant mission in the energy sector!

** About the role **

The Platform Services Team maintains, supports and operates AEMO’s high
availability Multi-cloud infrastructure. The infrastructure consists of a
national data network, AEMO owned private cloud, Public cloud and Cloud
Software Services offered by Azure. The role ensures policies align with
AEMO’s cyber-security framework to secure the infrastructure. This
infrastructure supports AEMO’s real-time data, voice, video and the Energy
Market systems essential to run the Australian Energy Markets.

This role requires innovative thought leadership to guide decision making on
new technologies and investments in AEMO infrastructure. It also needs to
bring a high level of expertise and is responsible for providing strategic
guidance on complex BAU and projects issues. This multicloud infrastructure is
critical to AEMO delivering highly available services to participants and is
essential to ensuring the security of the Energy markets and systems. The
challenge is to balance the operational availability demands and deploying
projects for new services in an environment that is undergoing rapid industry
change. Including rapidly expanding our service offering to move from
traditional energy resources to distributed managed renewable resources.

** Position Responsibilities **

  * Lead infrastructure, services, modernization and security initiatives 
  * Ensure that IT Platform systems and infrastructure are monitored and secured against internal and external threats, including risk management and information security. (E.g., Patching and upgrades) 
  * Maintain and extend in-depth technical knowledge across a broad range of technologies, including Server and security frameworks and best practices, storage and backup technologies and server hardware suppliers. 
  * Orchestrate, manage, and deliver different platforms. Develop and deliver business aligned technology to a roadmap. 
  * Effective leadership and mentoring of junior-mid level engineers with Strong Stakeholder management capabilities. 
  * Requires to be on the On-call roster 24*7 support to respond to incidents after hours (Rotation 1 in 8 weeks) 

** Position Requirements **

_ Skills & Experience _

  * Proven experience in Server, Storage and Data Protection technologies. E.g. Dell, Pure, Cohesity. 
  * Strong Infrastructure background (Servers, Storage, Virtualization) with proven experience in DevOps, Ansible, PowerShell. 
  * Proven experience in Data Centre infrastructure technology environments. 
  * Hands on technical experience with M365 & Azure 
  * Strong experience in a Multi-Cloud environment. 
  * Knowledge of industry best practices such as ITIL, Change Management, Quality Assurance Systems 
  * Experience working with Security frameworks and SIEM is preferred. 
  * Knowledge in containerisation, AKS, OpenShift. 

_ Education/ Certifications _

  * Degree qualifications in Computing and IT, Communications/Electronics Engineering or equivalent. 
  * Recognized professional certifications in VMware, Microsoft and server and storage hardware technologies. 
  * Certifications associated with Cloud services, Azure, AWS or Google 

** Our Values **

At AEMO, our core values aren’t just ‘words on a wall’ – we are a purpose-
based organization at the centre of our energy future, and we stand for our
values: ** Character, Connection & Commitment ** .

As we continue to innovate and work on some world-first, ground-breaking
projects, we need to attract the brightest people and provide opportunities to
contribute, stretch and grow. We actively encourage you to bring your whole
self to work, so that together we can do better, be better, and love our work.
For this reason, inviting difference and leading inclusively is a core part of
our culture. We challenge ourselves to take bold actions to improve the
experience for all our people, with a current focus on gender, flexibility,
(dis)ability and our First Nation peoples.

